<div id="review_592780124" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/592780124" />
    <a title="Freda Malone" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6938113-freda-malone"><img alt="Freda Malone" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1418039583p2/6938113.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/592780124?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Freda Malone" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Freda Malone" href="/user/show/6938113-freda-malone">Freda Malone</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6938113-freda-malone?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer592780124" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13132824721175004507">James Rollins is a brilliant writer. His works lure you through adventurous and historical events, both factual and fictional, that makes the readers feel like they are actually there, side by side with the Sigma Force of Monk, Kat, Painter Crowe, Gray and the Guild villains. I loved this book particularly because it centers on our founders (founding fathers) and the history of the growing claims of the United States, the Louisiana Purchase, Indian tribes, links between the bloodlines of our peo</span>
  <span id="freeText13132824721175004507" style="display:none">James Rollins is a brilliant writer. His works lure you through adventurous and historical events, both factual and fictional, that makes the readers feel like they are actually there, side by side with the Sigma Force of Monk, Kat, Painter Crowe, Gray and the Guild villains. I loved this book particularly because it centers on our founders (founding fathers) and the history of the growing claims of the United States, the Louisiana Purchase, Indian tribes, links between the bloodlines of our peoples and the nature of our volcanic mountains. I still can not comprehend all the scientific information Rollins creates, but it doesn't deter me from reading on, savoring the adventure of suspense and wonder of it all. I like that Rollins reveals what is truth and fictional in his books, otherwise I just might believe it all. A gripping addition to the Sigma series that had me at page 1. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13132824721175004507" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


