<div id="review_313026583" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/313026583" />
    <a title="Elizabeth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1832683-elizabeth"><img alt="Elizabeth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1232982633p2/1832683.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/313026583?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth" href="/user/show/1832683-elizabeth">Elizabeth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer313026583" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9469091598153333413">i picked this up at the airport because the little mason symbol on the cover completely reminded me of a friend who vehemently states (even as i question him incessantly at 3 in the morning) that he is <i>not</i> in the illuminati or whatever, which totally means that he is. <i>AND.</i> the inside read &quot;is the birth of the nation based on a lie?&quot; and i&apos;m all <i>holy shit</i> my mom&apos;s birth was based on a lie! really. it listed her as male for like 47 years until she, dragging her friend carol for moral support, went</span>
  <span id="freeText9469091598153333413" style="display:none">i picked this up at the airport because the little mason symbol on the cover completely reminded me of a friend who vehemently states (even as i question him incessantly at 3 in the morning) that he is <i>not</i> in the illuminati or whatever, which totally means that he is. <i>AND.</i> the inside read "is the birth of the nation based on a lie?" and i'm all <i>holy shit</i> my mom's birth was based on a lie! really. it listed her as male for like 47 years until she, dragging her friend carol for moral support, went to change it. funny gender reassignment story actually. it's better when my mom tells it because you would be all <i>"YOU LIED TO THEM?!? ...but you give communion! AT MASS!!"</i> ....ah, hilarity.<br /><br />anyway <i>this book was meant for me.</i> <br /><br />so yadda yadda yadda people dying cars exploding fort knox needs a whole lotta screen doors action awesomeness. so yeah. fun read. but. dude. <i>dude</i>. how come the bad guys always ALWAYS have someone deep undercover in like the top positions in every government/military installation or whatever. i've seen NCIS and Bones and Happy Endings so I know all about this and that it takes a whole hell of a lot to get security clearances. like background checking my dog serious screenings. how do we never catch the bad ones until it‘s too late and we are all like “hey, i always thought there was something wrong with fred. and now i‘m shot and bleeding out. thank you fred, sheesh. three days til retirement…arghbeaio39r59defijf…..” (that was me dying)<br /><br />and oh. OH. <i> and what about one of the good guys infiltrating the secret society?? </i> where's that shit? <i>sigh</i>. are we not smart enough people? hey wait...i'm smart. and i know my friend is in the <s>templars</s>. <s>illuminati</s>. <s>masons</s>. <s>skull and crossbones</s>. <s>pottery barn</s>? anyway. i know he's in something. i'm going to infiltrate it and save america. HELL YEAH.<br /><br />i would like to apologize to james rollins for this complete and utter sham of a review. gender reassignment? secret societies? this doesn't even make sense. just like the chewbacca defense. but i was rushed. my vicious pit bull/ american bulldog "The Bishop" wanted to play with his ball and crawled under my legs. thereby rendering complete thoughts almost impossible. he is so cute. he's the cutest little Bisha-Bo! yes he is! ....anyway. PITY ME.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9469091598153333413" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


